{
  "text": "Our first observation concerns the change of sign in \u03b8 with respect to k B h = \u03c0, owing to the 2\u03c0-periodicity of the spectrum in Re k B h, and its and reflection symmetry within that Brillouin zone period. Accordingly, \u2202\u03c9/\u2202k B changes sign, and hence so does P 1 , as noted by [CITATION_1] in his analysis of anti-plane shear. The diagram exhibits 2-fold rotational symmetry about (\u03c0, 0), which corresponds to \u03b8 i \u2248 30",
  "correct_citation": {
